sources.title: What Happened To Rosa (1921)
sources.description: WHAT HAPPENED TO ROSA Goldwyn 4,148 ft., rel. Apr. 23, 1921 dir. Victor L. Schertzinger, auth. Gerald C. Duffy from a story by Pearl Lenore Curran, cam. George Webber, film editors. Robert Bishop, Jack Dennis cast: Mabel Normand (Mayme Ladd, also Rosa Alvaro), Hugh Thompson (Dr. Maynard Drew), Tully Marshall (Percy Peacock), Doris Pawn (Gwen Applebaum), Eugenie Besserer (Madame Yvette O'Donnell), Buster Trow (Spike), Adolphe Menjou Location: Goldwyn studio, Culver City, CA, San Francisco, CA (exterior shots) copyright: Nov. 22, 1920 William Thomas Sherman, wts@gunjones.com, http://www.angelfire.com/mn/hp/

metadata.Plot: A fortune teller tells a store clerk with a romantic disposition that she was a Spanish noblewoman in an earlier life. The girl begins to live the part of the Spanish noblewoman and romance and comedy ensue.
metadata.Writer: Pearl Lenore Curran, Gerald C. Duffy
metadata.Actors: Mabel Normand, Doris Pawn, Tully Marshall
